quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  70,1,"A beseecher besought the visitation of chastisement,",footnotes:182286:1
  70,2,"(a chastisement meant) for the unbelievers, one which none can avert;"
  70,3,"a chastisement from Allah, the Lord of the ascending steps,",footnotes:182287:1
  70,4,"by which the angels and the Spirit ascend to Him in one Day the duration of which is fifty thousand years.",footnotes:182288:1,footnotes:182289:2,footnotes:182290:3
  70,5,"So, (O Prophet), persevere with gracious perseverance.",footnotes:182291:1
  70,6,"Verily they think that the chastisement is far off,"
  70,7,"while We think that it is near at hand.",footnotes:182292:1
  70,8,"It shall befall on a Day whereon the sky will become like molten brass,",footnotes:182293:1,footnotes:182294:2
  70,9,"and the mountains will become like dyed tufts of wool,",footnotes:182295:1
  70,10,"and no bosom friend will enquire about any of his bosom friends"